 <title>Building SAML v2.0 Service Providers With Fedlets</title>
 <indexterm>
  <primary>Fedlets</primary>
  <secondary>SAML v2.0</secondary>
 </indexterm>
 <para>This chapter introduces OpenAM Fedlets, and shows how to use the Fedlet
 as part of your Java web or .NET application.</para>

 <para>An OpenAM <firstterm>Fedlet</firstterm> is a small web application that
  that acts as a lightweight SAML v2.0 service provider. </para>
 <para>Fedlets are easy to integrate into Java and .NET web applications. The
  Fedlet does not require an entire OpenAM installation alongside your
  application, but instead can redirect to OpenAM for single sign on, and to
  retrieve SAML assertions.</para>

